node.title: Welcome to Charleston
node.description: The Pineapple Fountain in downtown Charleston, SC.  It may not be evident from this shot, but it sure is tough to shoot around sunset.  There must have been 15-20 kids swimming or jumping in the fountain.

node.title: Humming
node.description: My first attempt at shooting humming birds hand-held.  They have finally started coming around our feeders.  I can't seem to work fast enough to get them in focus very often.

node.title: The Fork
node.description: The Roaring Fork River in GSMNP, near Gatlinburg.

node.title: At the Mouth
node.description: The entrance to Little Lagoon Pass where it is fed by the Gulf.  The colors were sort of muted on this morning, so I went with a moody B&W composition.

node.title: "C" the Gator?
node.description: This gator took a big chomp out of something and turned quickly while we watched.  Gulf State Park, Gulf Shores, AL.

node.title: Colors of Minnehaha
node.description: Minnehaha Falls in Rabun County, GA.  I really liked the way the rust colored rocks contrasted with the vibrant greens in this shot.

node.title: Full Moon at Little Lagoon
node.description: Long exposure at Little Lagoon in Gulf Shores, AL.  A boat pulling into the ramp provided a nice streakyness to the water in the foreground.

node.title: Vanishing Point
node.description: Gulf State Park Pier in the early morning.

node.title: Going Vertical at Mardis Mill
node.description: It's tough to get a unique comp at Mardis, but this is my effort....shot from the rockslide about 150 yards from the falls.
